cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric cover problems in the plane and proposes algorithms for finding solutions for different types of planar objects. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents polynomial algorithms for finding reduced solution spaces. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with discretization of a continuous problem. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with finding a minimum cardinality collection of planar translates, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the complexity of the proposed algorithms.
